WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.214 --> 00:00:02.814
In here, we will demonstrate

2
00:00:02.843 --> 00:00:04.989
how a virus can crash your system.

3
00:00:07.414 --> 00:00:09.300
Here is a malicious program we made. 

4
00:00:09.500 --> 00:00:12.911
When activated by the user, it will start copying itself.

5
00:00:13.111 --> 00:00:17.523
Each window you will see is a copy of the virus trying to run.

6
00:00:19.114 --> 00:00:20.854
Now you can see it’s multiplying.

7
00:00:21.054 --> 00:00:24.971
That’s how a real virus spread. It's makes copies of itself

8
00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:27.859
so it can take over more parts of your system.

9
00:00:28.914 --> 00:00:30.200
As the copies pile up,

10
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:33.060
the computer slows down and becomes hard to use.

11
00:00:33.260 --> 00:00:36.829
This is because the virus is using up the system’s resources,

12
00:00:36.857 --> 00:00:38.291
like memory and CPU.

13
00:00:39.343 --> 00:00:41.049
This can lock people out of their work, 

14
00:00:41.249 --> 00:00:44.374
crash programs, and stop important tasks from running.

15
00:00:44.574 --> 00:00:46.414
Be careful.

